The paper deals with developing a probabilistic anticipation algorithm for dynamic objects observed by an autonomous robot in an urban environment. This involves the use of predictive Gaussian mixture models to capture continuous and discrete obstacle decisions and behaviors. The paper also proposes a Gaussian splitting method based on the sigma-point transform and the nonlinear dynamics function, which enables increased accuracy as the number of mixands grows. The paper's focus on autonomous robots and their interaction with the environment, as well as the use of probabilistic models and machine learning techniques, suggests that the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories are cs.RO (Robotics), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
